Solution of Homework 3

The choosen dataset

I chose a database from kaggle.com (Rajesh, 2023), that contains Netflix movies and TV-shows from 2015 to 2021.

Data transformation task

The first step is to filter the rows for the Movies (Figure 2). The type column contains the Movie category we need.

We would like to convert the variable duration into a categorical variable duration_fact. The variable duration contains the length of the movies in minutes. To do this, first review the descriptive statistical measures (Figure 2).

After looking at the minimum and maximum (3 and 312), we will create the following categories in a new ordinal scale variable (called duration_fact). Create a new transform (Figure 3). Insert a transformed variable in jamovi (Figure 4).

After performing the transformations, determine the distribution of the new variable duration_fact (Figure 5).

It can be seen that most films are between 90 and 120 minutes long.
